('YvzMpet3648', 'Filming in the stratosphere with a HTC mobile phone + fireworks at 20,000ft', 'Here we have footage shot at 106,500ft on a MOBILE PHONE. its amazing something that started life as a means of contact has developed into such a versatile piece of tech regardless of which you own. These HTC M8 phones have endured -65 air temps with just a few bits of polystyrene and duct tape to protect them and to celebrate this i let some fireworks off on the assent to this wonderful footage.\n\nMore info on my website here http://www.colinfurze.com\n\nsee part 1 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vbymuO3mRQ8&list=UUp68_FLety0O-n9QU6phsgw\n\nsee part 2 http://youtu.be/iyKU1UwUAqQ\n\nThe way we share what’s happening is changing. Find out how, at http://www.htc.com/creatography or search for #Creatography\n\nThe music is by a swedish band called HEROIC you can see them here - The song is called \"when thoughts collide\"\n\nWebsite: www.heroicofficial.com\nSpotify: https://play.spotify.com/album/164oRDAAP6ZTz9sU05tSYA\n\nTo find out more about High altitude balloons speak to Chris Hilcox at this website.\n\nhttps://balloonnews.wordpress.com\\\n\nTo get COLINFURZE MERCH click here\nhttps://www.colinfurzeshop.com', '2014-12-29', 1, 'The music is by a swedish band called HEROIC you can see them here - The song is called \"when thoughts collide\"\r\n\r\nWebsite: www.heroicofficial.com\r\nSpotify: https://play.spotify.com/album/164oRDAAP6ZTz9sU05tSYA'),
