('fGr0oifJMEI', 'World\'s Fastest Bumper Car - 600cc 100bhp But how FAST?', 'To get a COLINFURZE MERCH click here\nhttps://www.colinfurzeshop.com\n\nIt\'s finished and it\'s FAST....so fast its the worlds fastest as approved by Guinness World Records\nThis 600cc monster is the work of hours of shed time working out how to squeeze a sports bike and so wheels into a dodgem shell without making a death trap, but surprisingly in a straight line it\'s actually quite a solid ride, even when reaching 3 figure speeds.\nSo did i make a ride fit for The Stig..................I think so.\n\nSee how i made it here\nPart 1 https://youtu.be/tEQopnaHipo\nPart 2 https://youtu.be/oKANFyeGXxc\n\nOrder The Colin Furze book aimed at kids 6+ which is full of little projects to turn them into little inventors and loads of pictures of my previous projects http://smarturl.it/C-Furze\n\nThis is a sponsored project by BBC Worldwide\n\nCheck out Series 24 of Top Gear here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NyAKoKi-8k0\n\nSee the other Epic Vehicles i\'ve made and why i got given the job here\nhttps://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGjbAdaOBLBnaHyo8G3xt7cVTg5asaR3L\n\nSocial stuff here people\nTwitter https://twitter.com/colin_furze\nInstagram https://www.instagram.com/realcolinfurze/\nFacebook https://www.facebook.com/Colin-furze-521680751253584\n\nMUSIC\n\n1st Track is called \"Point of no Return\" and the 2nd \"Valentino\" both tracks are by \"March to the Grave\" More on them here\nhttps://itunes.apple.com/us/album/point-of-no-return/id508264221?i=508264289&uo=4\n\nIn a band, want your music on my videos! Send your tracks to furzemail@yahoo.co.uk as all music on this channel is from viewer\'s.', '2017-03-30', 1, '1st Track is called \"Point of no Return\" and the 2nd \"Valentino\" both tracks are by \"March to the Grave\" More on them here\r\nhttps://itunes.apple.com/us/album/point-of-no-return/id508264221?i=508264289&uo=4'),
