('jsg6uOTljkQ', 'How to build a TURBOJET ENGINE-The Oil System and controls', 'Your Turbojet engine needs oil and you need to be able to control it so here is an over view of how i did mine. You need to have oil preasure of around 15psi - 65psi max (so i,m told) so having a manual bypass is very helpful as when engine spinning fast and oil is hot things change so one setting will not work.\n\nCheck my other pages for news and pictures\nTwitter https://twitter.com/colin_furze\nInstagram https://www.instagram.com/realcolinfurze/\nFacebook https://www.facebook.com/Colin-furze-521680751253584\nhttp://www.colinfurze.com\n\nThe ignitors are from ebay here\n\nhttp://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/230801362045?ssPageName=STRK:MEWNX:IT&_trksid=p3984.m1497.l2649\n\nAnd the regulators here\n\nhttp://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/AR2000-Air-Control-Compressor-Pressure-Relief-Regulating-Regulator-Valve-Gauge-/390568240629?pt=LH_DefaultDomain_3&hash=item5aefae65f5\n\nIts all chinesse shit but means you can build this thing cheap.\n\nto see it in action go here\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QxpHJipB67g\n\nSHABBA', '2013-08-22', 1, NULL),
