('vuRV-uXGy1w', 'Making a Motorised Go Cart with NO WELDER and simple tools #1 - Chassis/Engine', 'To get a COLINFURZE MERCH click here\nhttps://www.colinfurzeshop.com\n\nLots of people don\'t have the luxury of a well kitted out workshop but still want to make stuff, they just don\'t always know where to start.\nSo this project is for those people (which was me not so long ago)\n\nPART 2 OUT NEXT THURSDAY/FURZEDAY SUBSCRIBE\n\nAll the parts were bought from http://www.pitbikeparts.co.uk\nThis is not a sponsored video just thought its easier if everything comes from one place, they know what i\'ve had so if you undertake this project and need any of the parts just call them and they will sort you out.\n\nA picture Gallery will be uploaded to my website next week when project is complete.\n\nCheck out these other projects https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGjbAdaOBLBnaHyo8G3xt7cVTg5asaR3L\n\nFollow me on social media here\nTwitter https://twitter.com/colin_furze\nInstagram https://www.instagram.com/realcolinfurze/\nFacebook https://www.facebook.com/Colin-furze-521680751253584\n\nMusic is by \"Across the Atlas\" and the songs are \"jaded\" and \"TV killed the radio star\"\nFind out more from them here\nhttps://www.facebook.com/acrosstheatlas/\nhttps://soundcloud.com/acrosstheatlas\nhttps://www.youtube.com/user/acrosstheatlas', '2016-10-27', 1, 'Music is by \"Across the Atlas\" and the songs are \"jaded\" and \"TV killed the radio star\"\r\nFind out more from them here\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/acrosstheatlas/\r\nhttps://soundcloud.com/acrosstheatlas\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/user/acrosstheatlas'),
